 and published sources, this book reconstructs how the former physicist initiated his work in phage biology and achieved his landmark investigation. The account of Benzer’s creativity as a researcher is a fascinating story that also reveals intriguing aspects common to the scientific enterprise.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBacterial genomes. 0aBacteriophagesxGenetics. 0aGene mapping. 0aGeneticistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMicrobial genetics. 0aViral geneticsxHistory. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Genetics & Genomics.2bisacsh1 aSummers, William C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSummers, William C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030011078440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012970040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129700423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129700/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY